<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="62" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="5" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,337,1931,1957]" pageId="5" pageNumber="62">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is composed of “hetero” (different in Greek) and “picta” (painted in Latin) and refers to the color pattern of the species, which is different from that found in the species described above. Adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
